MASTERS TOURNAMENT
April 5, 2018
Marc Leishman
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 Q. (No Microphone.)  
MARC LEISHMAN: I drove the ball pretty well on the back nine, the ‑‑ the putter was still pretty good. Obviously disappointing double on 15, but this place can do that to you if you hit it in the wrong spot you're in trouble and I was there.   
   
 Q. Tell us about the crowds?  
MARC LEISHMAN: The crowds were great. Obviously a lot of people out there on the biggest stage, so it's nice to be on that stage and play well. Luckily if I'm going to be contending for the Tournament, which hopefully I am Sunday afternoon, I'll be feeling the same sort of thing. So I look at it as a positive playing with Tiger, he's a great guy and we spoke a lot out there and yeah, it was cool playing in front of big crowds like that. I really enjoy it.   
   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT